HEADWORD: Thrum-eyed
<hw>Thrum"-eyed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having the anthers raised above the stigma, and visible at the
throat of the corolla, as in long-stamened primroses; -- the reverse of
<xex>pin-eyed</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thrummy</ent>⟦br⟧
